<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>Hi All:<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>I&#8217;ve written an openmpi program that &#8220;self
schedules&#8221; the work. &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>The master task is in a loop chunking up an input stream and
handing off jobs to worker tasks.&nbsp; At first the master gives the next job
to the next highest rank. &nbsp;After all ranks have their first job, the
master waits via an MPI receive call for the next free worker.&nbsp; The master
parses out the rank from the MPI receive and sends the next job to this node. &nbsp;The
jobs aren&#8217;t all identical, so they run for slightly different durations based
on the input data.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>When I plot a histogram of the number of jobs each worker
performed, the lower mpi ranks are doing much more work than the higher ranks. &nbsp;For
example, in a 120 process run, rank 1 did 32 jobs while rank 119 only did 2. &nbsp;My
guess is that openmpi returns the lowest rank from the MPI Recv when I&#8217;ve
got MPI_ANY_SOURCE set and multiple sends have happened since the last call.<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>Is there a different Recv call to make that will spread out the
data better?<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>THANXS!<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><font size=2 face=Arial><span style='font-size:10.0pt;
font-family:Arial'>amb<o:p></o:p></span></font></p>

